# A bare expression with no effect -- here a lone identifier -- is not a valid
# statement; it is almost always an incomplete line (e.g. a truncated `x = ...`).
# Both compilers must reject it: only a call may stand alone as a statement.
# (This locks the hierc/hierc0 parity the reject fuzzer flagged: hierc used to
# accept a bare identifier statement that hierc0 rejected.)
fn main():
    x := 5
    x
